   Purpose:
        Random table updates on a very large table
        upto half of global memory

	If the output from bench13 specifies (passed) then 
	the program ran 99% error free which is acceptable, 
	otherwise, (failed) will appear.
 

	1. ./bin/bench13
	   Binary executable for MPI Guppie pthreads

################################################################################
# Usage		:
#
	./bench13 <nthreads> <ltabsize> <lnupdate> # e.g. "./bench13 2 24 27> 
################################################################################
# Parameters		:
#
#
	nthreads - Number threads to process updates.
	ltabsize - Large table size in Megabytes
	lnupdate - 
Output:


################################################################################
# Compile		:
./src/Makefile will call the subdirectory Makefiles in the 
./src/src/EZThreads/src and 
./src/src

To build from the subdirectories:
Must first do make to create the archive library
Second do make to create the bench13 executable

Addition compilation notes:
  -how to compile in general: cc -D_REENTRANT -o bench13 bench13.c -lpthread libEZThreads.a
  -you might need more options to tell the compiler to load
  reentrant versions of the standard C libraries
  -or maybe you might need something like -D_REENTRANT on the compile-line  
  -on the DEC you need the -pthread option to do this
  
  -compile DEC: cc -pthread -o bench13 bench13.c libEZThreads.a
  -compile HP:  cc +DD64 -D_POSIX_C_SOURCE=199506L -o bench13 bench13.c -lpthread libEZThreads.a
  -compile Sun: cc -mt -xO3 -xarch=v9 -o bench13 bench13.c -lpthread libEZThreads.a
